Assent Compliance is the global leader in supply chain data management. We combine leading-edge technology with supply chain expertise to help companies collect and manage the data they need to comply with global requirements and make ethical business decisions. As the leader in the industry, we’re growing fast, and we’re looking for passionate, energetic people to join our team!
Learn more about us here!
As a co-op on our software development team, you will gain practical experience with the whole web development stack, from server to front-end. You will work closely with more experienced engineers to create new features, advancing your skills and the Assent Compliance Platform at the same time. Through your passion for software development, developing object-oriented design skills, you will produce quality code and proactively communicate with other stakeholders regarding business requirements. Most importantly, you will demonstrate a deep desire and capability to further your knowledge and experience.
You'll be working on:
Be a functional Scrum team member;
Break down and estimate business needs, translating them into functional and technical requirements;
Solve customer problems using our software stack of C#/.Net in the back-end, Angular in the front-end;
Write unit tests and acceptance tests based on functionality built;
Adhere to Assent Compliance design guidelines, coding standards and security guidelines.
Qualifications:
Interest in pursuing a Software Engineering or Computer Science program;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English;
Developing ability to apply engineering principles to identify issues, develop solutions, and recommend improvements;
Self-starter initiative with a proactive approach to problem identification and resolution;
Excellent organizational skills and ability to manage multiple priorities and timelines;
Proficient skill in the use of MS Office Suite and Google Applications;
Great interpersonal skills- you are able to establish cross-functional relationships in a collaborative team-based environment to achieve shared goals;
Grit - you are conscientious, will always work towards providing solutions over excuses and are dedicated to achieving excellence and driving results;
An open to feedback mindset, coachable and are always striving to self-improve;
An insatiable thirst for knowledge - you consider yourself a lifelong learner;
Curiosity and motivation to learn and keep up-to-date with new web technologies and approaches;
The ability adapt quickly to changing business needs – you thrive in a fast-paced, ever-changing environment;
Strong understanding of the importance of documentation and process.
What’s in it for you?
At Assent, we are an ambitious, fast-paced business which means there is never a dull moment. We strive to give back to our employees as much as they give to us.
Here are only some of the skills and projects you’ll have an opportunity to learn and contribute to during your term:
Experience in working inside a Scrum team using the Agile Software Development Life-cycle (SDLC);
Experience in writing small decoupled microservices using C#/.NET;
Experience in front-end development using HTML, CSS and Javascript inside the AngularJS or Angular framework;
Experience in writing Test-Driven Development (TDD) using NUnit, Jasmin, Mocha, Chai and/or Selenium;
In addition to advancing your career, you can expect to:
Love what you do as part of a supportive team with a fantastic culture.
Choose how you work best in a flexible work environment.
Help create positive change by being part of a sustainable work environment with lots of opportunities to help the Ottawa community through our charitable work
Upon offer of employment, a successful candidate will need to fulfill the requirements necessary to obtain a background check.
Job Types: Internship, Apprenticeship

