Analyst-programmer
The programmer analyst combines the roles and responsibilities of the functional analyst and the programmer. The analyst-programmer thus combines skills in analysis and design, with the ability to use tools and programming languages to achieve computerized solutions. It performs unit testing and supports functional testing to ensure that systems are properly tested and meet specifications.
Activities
- Support clients during the development and definition of their needs;
- Write and / or modify functional analysis and test deliverables;
- Produce all relevant documentation, specific to his field of expertise, according to the norms and standards (Macroscope methodology);
- Participate in the validation of certain detailed architecture deliverables;
- Support the coordinator in the preparation and coordination of the work plans required for the execution of the works;
- Participate in the development of solutions (design of approaches responding to technical constraints);
- Carry out the development necessary for the adaptation of the modules identified by the architects and / or analysts;
- Perform the programming;
- Perform unit and functional tests;
- Participate in follow-up meetings with the implementation team and report on its level of progress, possible solutions and / or problems that could compromise the timelines or the completion of the project;
- Ensure that the deadlines for the mandates under his charge are respected;
- Support the project manager in the preparation and coordination of the work plans required for the execution of the work if required;
- Design system prototypes according to user needs;
- Write functional and / or organic specifications of varying complexity;
- Carry out programs of varying complexity in accordance with the specifications of the functional analyzes;
- Diagnose and solve technical problems of varying complexity in applications and programmed modules;
- Make adjustments to functional files during anomalies and supervise the fixes with the production team;
- Support simulation tests during production releases;
- Participate in the implementation and production support;
- Deliver the software solution incrementally;
- Demonstrate the results obtained at the end of each iteration;
- Obtain the necessary authorizations relating to the quality assurance program;
- Carry out modifications and additions to components in collaboration with the software architecture consultant.
Fluent French written and spoken is a must/ English is an asset
Minimum requirements
1. Have five(5) years of professional experience in information technology.
2. Have worked in a mandate having applied the principles of the Agile realization methodology.
3. Have knowledge of programming in a .Net environment using among others: VB, C #, Visual Studio (ILS, ASP, etc.) or knowledge of JAVA programming using among others: JAVA, Javascript, Angular 4.0 and + as well as Jasmine.
4. Have experience with object-oriented concepts and some of the following technologies: MVC5, MVW, AJAX, REST / SOAP, Bootstrap, JQuery, JSON etc.).
5. Have knowledge of Team Foundation Server (TFS) 2012 or a newer version or other source manager tool with functionality similar to TFS (example GIT).
6. Have carried out mandates using development methods similar to those used in the Department (DMR-P2 and P3).
